just_use mine_doomed_growing.py

# label: TOOL (OPTIMIZE_PYTHON era)
# role: search the BFS frontier for states with doomed growing partials

The doomed-third filter checks at MERGE time: a 2-partial
admitted to growing must have a completion candidate in the
inventory at admission. It does NOT re-check existing
growing partials when subsequent moves consume their
candidates elsewhere.

This script walks the BFS frontier of a captured snapshot
case looking for states where some growing 2-partial has
NO completion candidate in the CURRENT-state inventory.
Reports per-projection stats + sample.

Result on the slowest captured case (2026-04-25): 74% of
states in the worst projection had a doomed growing
partial. Drove the state-level doomed-growing filter that
landed in `bfs_solver.enumerate_moves`.

Use case: validating that the state-level filter still
catches what it should, OR investigating a new
runaway-shape if one emerges.

```
python3 mine_doomed_growing.py /tmp/perf_snapshots.jsonl
    [--max-states N]
    [--rank N]   # 1 = slowest snapshot, etc.
```

## Pointers

- `bfs_solver._has_doomed_third` + state-level filter at
  the top of `enumerate_moves` — what this tool helped
  validate.
- `test_bfs_enumerate.py::test_doomed_growing_partial_is_reachable`
  — pinned regression test.
